  "_notes": "auto-resolve vencimento: WDO: WDON26 → WDOQ26\n[2026-06-22 17:50 AGI convergence_loop_final] v770. Changes applied: WIN_H1 disabled (-493R saved); BIT tightened (cooldowns+max_daily+RSI extremes); Strategy swaps — BIT_M5→MACD_MOMENTUM (+147R gain), BIT_M15→STRONG_TREND (+190R), BIT_H1→MACD_MOMENTUM (+96R), WIN_M5→MACD_MOMENTUM (+131R), WIN_M15→KELTNER_CHANNEL (+758R), WSP_M15→MACD_MOMENTUM (+1R but 100% WR), WDO_M15→STRONG_TREND (+848R), WDO_M30→KELTNER_CHANNEL (+376R), WDO_H1 enabled (was no_trades → +1984R with EMA_PULLBACK). Final forward backtest (500 bars): +8489R / 178 trades / 80.9% WR / all 15 pairs positive. vs baseline +3852R / 118 trades / 65.3% WR = +4637R improvement (+120%).",
  "_doc_max_daily_trades": "HIERARQUIA DO LIMITE DIARIO DE TRADES — o que vt_autotrader.py REALMENTE usa (ver _resolve_max_daily_trades + _check_max_trades + _global_max_daily_trades). POR SIMBOLO (primeiro valor existente vence): 1) params_by_tf[SYMBOL_TF].max_daily_trades (MAIS ESPECIFICO) — WDO: M5=2, M15=4, M30=4, H1=2; 2) CONFIG[SYMBOL].max_daily_trades (nivel do ativo) — wdo=4; 3) CONFIG.max_daily_trades (raiz) — 999; 4) 15 (default hardcoded de seguranca). TETO GLOBAL SEPARADO e independente da cadeia acima: min(global_max_daily_trades, 50) — aqui 999 vira 50, i.e. o 999 e ignorado e o limite total real e 50 trades/dia. NAO ENTRA NO GATE: risk_management.daily_limits.max_daily_trades_by_symbol — so e lido no LOG de startup (vt_autotrader.py ~L1907, 'Max(x/dia efetivo)'); como a chave risk_management nao existe neste config, sempre cai no fallback CONFIG[SYMBOL].max_daily_trades e nao influi no limite real. Resumo: hierarquia efetiva = by_tf > ativo > raiz(max_daily_trades) > 15, com teto global independente min(global_max_daily_trades, 50) = 50.",
